node.text:
Imagine a problem, a concern, or hurdle you currently have in your life.  That problem concern or hurdle is equal to your current level of awareness (consciousness) as it relates to that problem.  When we know how to expand our feeling inside our body, our inspiration, our joy, we can then become more expansive than the level of consciousness we were holding when we perceived the issue as a problem, concern, or hurdle in our lives. This doesn’t mean we don’t need to address the issue, but when we expand our level of awareness all of a sudden what we once perceived as a problem is now a simple pebble in the middle of the road we simply need to step over. 

Follow @DavidSamuelStraus  for more daily wisdom!

What is your takeaway from this video? Share it with me in the comments below!👇

node.title: How to solve a problem with @DavidSamuelStraus 🧐

node.text:
Your language to the universe is frequency! The word consciousness is thrown about so casually that it’s easy to lose sight of what it means, even more so when it is defined as being “awakened.” Awakened consciousness is a state of being aware that you are aware. It is a realization that you are the watcher, the witness within you—not the analyzer, not the thinker, not even the meditator, but that which is the impartial witness of every aspect of your being and doing. 

Follow @MichaelbBeckwith for more!

node.title: Follow @MichaelbBeckwith for more wisdom on the law of attraction!✨

May be an image of text that says 'ever in a stressful situation If you try this tip: inhale a deep breath to the count of 4, hold that breath in for 4 seconds before you exhale, exhale slowly to the count of 4, then hold for 4 seconds. Repeat as many times as needed. Nelia Torkian'.

node.text: Follow @NeliaTorkian for more quotes and captions like this! “Too often we move through life forgetting that we ALREADY possess one of the most powerful resources that we could ever even dream of—our breath. Regardless of what is going on outside of us and the ways that other people are or are not reacting to us, we ALWAYS have the power to pause and take our power back by consciously controlling our breath. Try it. You’ll find that intentionally becoming aware of your breathing and remembering to take deep deliberate breaths will put you fully in the present and change your perspective. In fact, taking an extra moment to pause and check in with yourself will also connect you on a deeper level to the true reality of whatever situation you currently find yourself in. It’ll help you better identify what exactly is triggering you or the other person and how you can best move through the situation with wisdom and ease. That’s why it’s so important to not only practice mindful breathing in moments of difficulty but also regularly throughout the day so that we can move through life being as fully present as possible. Because when you are fully in the moment, you’ll find that the ultimate truth that mindfulness will remind you of is how precious beyond measure it is to even be alive and to have a moment to go through the true miracle that is life. In the face of this fact, all other issues will—rightfully—seem insignificant”
